de.sciss.swingosc
Class ListResponder

java.lang.Object
  de.sciss.swingosc.AbstractResponder
      de.sciss.swingosc.ListResponder
All Implemented Interfaces:
EventListener, ListSelectionListener
public class ListResponder
extends AbstractResponder
implements ListSelectionListener

A ListResponder is created for a JList component. When instantiating, the responder starts to listen to ListSelectionEvents fired from that component's model, until remove is called. When an event occurs, the responder will send a /list OSC message to the client that has created the responder, with the first argument being the component's ID, followed by the state change selectionChanged, followed key-value pairs of properties. The property key names are specified in he constructor.
